                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.8227/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Walton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-29T14:00:00-00:44"
                            >May 29, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 29—12:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Department’s telegram No. 16, May 2, 4 p.m. Liberian Government agrees to
                    article III but suggests that article be omitted from <pb facs="0623" n="617"
                        xml:id="pg_617"/> text of the agreement and that article be ratified by an
                    exchange of notes. Question of favored nation clause raised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
